review_reply.reply_text: Thanks for your valuable feedback.Sir..As per norms,the maximum waiting time is 30 minutes from the scheduled time..For eg..if booked for 10.15,our doctors will consult  within the stipulated time period.As per your feedback the doctor came before 30 minutes to attend your child.Removal of footwear outside clinic premises is a safety protocol followed in our clinic to prevent transmission of infection as we handle  infants and senior citizens as well..We care for the safety of every individual visiting our practice.The doctor did not personally communicate or interact with the patient in this regard..Instead he instructed (not shouted) his receptionist as it's the duty of our team to tell them to do so which was missed in your case.. Nevertheless,we apologise for instructing the receptionist in front of you if it has hurt you personally. We also inform that we couldn't avoid it as it's a matter of negligence on safety precautions in this regard.Best wishes for your good health..
